summary: So I’m watching a mini-documentary about homelessness in Japan and they’re talking about public housing, which is usually big...
body:
So I’m watching a mini-documentary about homelessness in Japan and they’re talking about public housing, which is usually big concrete block style housing that typically has large numbers on them. Usually single women with children. 

Sound familiar?

I know it’s always brought up that Uraraka’s family doesn’t have much money, but… yeah, idk if this is something that most people noticed. Makes you wonder what Mr. Midoriya is getting up to at that overseas job he apparently has.

summary:
Sero Hanta : Have you seen Midoriya?
Todoroki Shouto : Who the hell is Midoriya?
Sero Hanta : Oh, sorry. I forget you pronounce...
body:
Sero Hanta : Have you seen Midoriya?
Todoroki Shouto : Who the hell is Midoriya?
Sero Hanta : Oh, sorry. I forget you pronounce it... [inhaling intensely] ...Meeh-doh-reeh-yaaaaah.
Todoroki Shouto : Oh, him! Well, yeah, you've got to pronounce the "H"s in it.
Sero Hanta : What? There are no "H"s in it!
Todoroki Shouto : THERE AREN'T?!!!
